1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,400
What if robots could learn from their mistakes just like us?

2
00:00:04,400 --> 00:00:07,200
They use a method called reinforcement learning.

3
00:00:07,200 --> 00:00:10,000
It's all about trial, reward, and policy.

4
00:00:10,000 --> 00:00:16,000
In this process, a robot tries different actions, gets feedback, and learns the best approach.

5
00:00:16,000 --> 00:00:17,600
But there's a catch!

6
00:00:17,600 --> 00:00:20,400
Simulated environments often don't match real life.

7
00:00:20,400 --> 00:00:25,600
This sim-to-real gap means a robot may struggle when faced with actual tasks.

8
00:00:25,600 --> 00:00:28,000
Curious about how robotics will evolve?

9
00:00:28,000 --> 00:00:30,400
Hit like and follow for more!
